      <!-- Text Block -->
      <div class="about center">
        <h3>Technology</h3>
        <p class="project__description">
          The overall stack is built around Flask (Python), using HTML, Jinja,
          and Bootstrap to achieve a scalable site that still looks good. The
          site also utilizes vanilla JavaScript along with AJAX to handle asynchronous
          file post requests, as well as the URL callback upon upload completion.
          The server runs behind an NGINX and UWSGI instance, to handle efficient
          routing with multiple requests at once.
        </p>
      </div>

      
      <!-- Text Block -->
      <div class="about center">
        <p class="project__description">
          Another interesting note is that this site was fully developed around CI / CD.
          The application is built into a Docker container hosted on Docker Hub. I use a
          webhook system to notify the Kubernetes cluster that runs the site, that a new
          image is ready to be downloaded.  
        </p>
      </div>

